to keep you out of it.

06:10.203 --> 06:12.973
What's she's doing
to Mr. Walter is wrong.

06:13.006 --> 06:14.642
Giving him them pills.

06:14.675 --> 06:18.145
He doesn't know, but I see her.

06:18.178 --> 06:21.915
A man his age--
he needs his ease.

06:21.949 --> 06:24.685
Does he know what's going on?
In general.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.987
He was brilliant.

06:27.020 --> 06:32.826
Now he's got gaps.
Big, empty spaces.

06:32.860 --> 06:34.562
Oh, she don't like me
to be late.

06:34.595 --> 06:37.230
Okay.
Thank you coming in.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.335
Well, the housekeeper confirms.

06:42.369 --> 06:44.538
Okay, so Mr. Walter
as in Walter Briggs, the writer?

06:44.572 --> 06:46.206
Yeah, Pulitzer Prize,
National Book Award.

06:46.239 --> 06:47.941
Well, he's nearly 80,
and his wife--

06:47.975 --> 06:50.110
